1
00:00:00,032 --> 00:00:03,746
[Previously]
The new volunteer seems kind of strange.

2
00:00:03,746 --> 00:00:07,521
If you came up here just to drink, I think you should go back.

3
00:00:07,521 --> 00:00:09,770
It's true we're here because we did something bad.

4
00:00:09,770 --> 00:00:14,625
But my friend isn't here just to find a place to drink as you thought.

5
00:00:14,625 --> 00:00:17,271
I won't tell the Village Headman about the other day,

6
00:00:17,271 --> 00:00:21,080
but if you do anything awful again, I won't let it go.

7
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:24,338
Please keep your eyes on me well, Khun Khru.

8
00:00:24,338 --> 00:00:26,731
Please take care of me.

9
00:00:35,278 --> 00:00:36,878
Fah.

10
00:00:39,126 --> 00:00:41,173
Fah, are you up?

11
00:00:53,293 --> 00:00:55,986
- Don't you have to work today?
- Yes.

12
00:00:56,794 --> 00:00:59,694
Let me sleep for a bit longer, though.

13
00:01:02,752 --> 00:01:04,849
Hey, try to take care of yourself.

14
00:01:04,849 --> 00:01:07,829
All you do is drink. Aren't you afraid of it destroying your body?

15
00:01:07,829 --> 00:01:09,891
Have you ever gotten a health check-up?

16
00:01:09,891 --> 00:01:13,960
Why would I? The doctor is sleeping right here.

17
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:19,767
Just hurry and get up. I need to get to class.

18
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:22,767
Don't be late for work, all right?

19
00:01:23,763 --> 00:01:25,793
Get to class, Dao.

20
00:01:35,510 --> 00:01:36,708
Hi, there.

21
00:01:36,708 --> 00:01:38,220
Are you leaving already?

22
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:41,984
The little brother left, but the big brother is still here.

23
00:01:43,288 --> 00:01:46,088
Wow! This is good.

24
00:01:46,088 --> 00:01:49,341
You are so good, Baby.

25
00:01:50,726 --> 00:01:53,266
Why are you breathing so heavily?

26
00:01:53,914 --> 00:01:55,514
Baby.

27
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,960
Babe.

28
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:03,878
Hey! How did you get in here?

29
00:02:03,878 --> 00:02:05,613
Oh, hey, Little Gong.

30
00:02:05,613 --> 00:02:08,034
You're here. I've been looking for you.

31
00:02:08,034 --> 00:02:10,418
Come on. Let's go home.

32
00:02:12,538 --> 00:02:14,339
I'm leaving now, Khun.

33
00:02:14,339 --> 00:02:17,701
Bye, Khun. Wait! Hold on!

34
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:22,460
Well... how did that pig get into my room?

35
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:23,880
The children raised it.

36
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:26,214
They took it out for a walk and it

37
00:02:26,214 --> 00:02:27,680
must have wandered off and into your house.

38
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,653
Take the pig back with you then.

39
00:02:29,653 --> 00:02:31,944
I'll continue my sleep.

40
00:02:31,944 --> 00:02:33,853
Please deal with it.

41
00:02:33,853 --> 00:02:35,680
Wait, Khun.

42
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:39,615
Don't you have to conduct a health check-up on the villagers today?

43
00:02:39,615 --> 00:02:41,360
That's on the ninth.

44
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:44,642
- And what's the date today?
- The sixth.

45
00:02:44,642 --> 00:02:46,300
Today is the ninth.

46
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,437
The sixth.

47
00:02:47,437 --> 00:02:49,802
Just check the calendar there.

48
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:09,830
[Mek JirakitThawornwong | Mark Jiruntanin Trairattanayon]

49
00:03:11,670 --> 00:03:16,130
♫ Taking a journey, no matter how far the horizon ♫

50
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:20,920
♫ No matter how high or steep the mountain ♫

51
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:28,820
♫ But in the end, it's too late, love vanished ♫

52
00:03:28,820 --> 00:03:33,290
♫ Until I met you halfway ♫

53
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:37,740
♫ Just like that, the sky brightened ♫

54
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:46,750
♫ Don't know why when you're close, it gives me the strength to keep walking ♫

55
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:51,530
♫ Do you think that our love really exists? ♫

56
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:54,570
[Star and Sky│Sky in your heart]

57
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:57,590
[Series Director: Siwat Sawatmaneekul]

58
00:04:02,199 --> 00:04:03,790
The first patient, please come in.

59
00:04:03,790 --> 00:04:05,702
Please have a seat.

60
00:04:05,702 --> 00:04:08,145
- Open your mouth, please.
- Should I take it off?

61
00:04:08,145 --> 00:04:11,089
No! Not that. I mean…

62
00:04:11,089 --> 00:04:12,645
Hey, Viah.

63
00:04:12,645 --> 00:04:14,924
Come. Let's get your weight.

64
00:04:14,924 --> 00:04:16,791
I'm 30 kilograms.

65
00:04:16,791 --> 00:04:18,670
30…

66
00:04:20,195 --> 00:04:21,181
What?

67
00:04:21,181 --> 00:04:23,311
I'm feeling hot.

68
00:04:23,311 --> 00:04:26,164
I might have a fever.

69
00:04:26,164 --> 00:04:27,992
Not like that, Viah.

70
00:04:27,992 --> 00:04:31,060
When weighing yourself, you must stand on it with both feet.

71
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:35,344
It's okay. I'll just go with 30 kilograms. I like it that way.

72
00:04:35,344 --> 00:04:36,840
- Come on, Viah!
- No, I won't.

73
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,381
- Viah, get on the scale!
- No, I don't want to!

74
00:04:38,381 --> 00:04:39,895
That's normal body temperature.

75
00:04:39,895 --> 00:04:42,310
No. I'm feeling so hot.

76
00:04:42,310 --> 00:04:45,128
If you don't believe me, feel it.

77
00:04:47,139 --> 00:04:48,428
I feel the sweat.

78
00:04:48,428 --> 00:04:51,403
Did you stand out in the sun?

79
00:04:53,432 --> 00:04:55,719
- Get on the scale!
- I don't want to!

80
00:04:55,719 --> 00:04:57,605
Gosh, you're strong!

81
00:04:58,971 --> 00:05:00,571
Viah.

82
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:03,557
Don't be stubborn.

83
00:05:03,557 --> 00:05:06,107
- Khru Prince.
- We've discussed this.

84
00:05:06,107 --> 00:05:08,684
You must behave when you're out and about.

85
00:05:08,684 --> 00:05:10,384
Okay.

86
00:05:13,137 --> 00:05:14,658
I knew this would happen.

87
00:05:14,658 --> 00:05:17,630
So the Village Headman sent me to help you.

88
00:05:22,643 --> 00:05:27,868
Loong Phang, please step on the weighing scale first.

89
00:05:27,868 --> 00:05:30,745
This thing keeps moving.

90
00:05:30,745 --> 00:05:33,369
It's making me dizzy.

91
00:05:33,369 --> 00:05:36,126
I don't think anything is wrong with the scale.

92
00:05:36,126 --> 00:05:38,740
I think it's you, Loong.

93
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:40,646
How about this, we don't have to get a weight right now.

94
00:05:40,646 --> 00:05:43,995
Let him have a seat first.

95
00:05:45,809 --> 00:05:48,423
- Hello, Doctor.
- I'm over here, Loong!

96
00:05:48,423 --> 00:05:51,545
Why didn't you tell me?

97
00:05:51,545 --> 00:05:54,462
- Hello.
- Hello.

98
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:03,487
Okay, then. Open your mouth, please.

99
00:06:08,322 --> 00:06:10,659
The smell of alcohol is quite strong, Loong.

100
00:06:11,494 --> 00:06:13,566
Are you drunk so early in the day again?

101
00:06:13,566 --> 00:06:17,720
It's just once in a while that I drink with my friends.

102
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,782
What do you mean, "once in a while," Loong?

103
00:06:19,782 --> 00:06:21,889
I see you drinking every day.

104
00:06:21,889 --> 00:06:23,789
You know me so well, Khru.

105
00:06:23,789 --> 00:06:26,294
I'm right here, Loong.

106
00:06:26,294 --> 00:06:29,294
Who moved you here?

107
00:06:36,613 --> 00:06:38,442
All right, Khun.

108
00:06:39,098 --> 00:06:42,101
You can let the next patient in.

109
00:06:42,101 --> 00:06:43,880
Hold on, Khun.

110
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,728
Aren't you going to have lunch?

111
00:06:45,728 --> 00:06:47,640
The Village Headman sent you a lunch box.

112
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:50,080
You can eat first.

113
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,900
I will continue the check-ups.

114
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:56,523
I will help then.

115
00:06:59,245 --> 00:07:01,620
Go ahead and eat first.

116
00:07:02,304 --> 00:07:07,027
A youngster like you must eat lots of food, do you know?

117
00:07:07,027 --> 00:07:11,741
If you don't eat, how will you have the energy to work?

118
00:07:11,741 --> 00:07:13,323
What about you?

119
00:07:13,323 --> 00:07:15,681
You haven't had breakfast, right?

120
00:07:15,681 --> 00:07:18,556
Where will you get the source of energy to work?

121
00:07:22,676 --> 00:07:24,276
Okay.

122
00:07:25,244 --> 00:07:29,208
If I eat, we're good?

123
00:07:30,147 --> 00:07:31,947
Okay.

124
00:07:34,012 --> 00:07:36,477
This is my lunch, right?

125
00:07:38,622 --> 00:07:41,361
Don't I get an omelet, too?

126
00:07:41,361 --> 00:07:43,327
The Village Headman made it.

127
00:07:43,327 --> 00:07:45,310
Of course, there's no omelet.

128
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:51,702
Honestly speaking, his food is good,

129
00:07:51,702 --> 00:07:53,826
but it's just a bit too spicy.

130
00:07:53,826 --> 00:07:57,851
To be honest,

131
00:07:58,954 --> 00:08:01,654
your omelet and rice...

132
00:08:02,452 --> 00:08:05,350
was really good for my soul.

133
00:08:06,995 --> 00:08:08,964
What an overstatement.

134
00:08:08,964 --> 00:08:10,565
Quickly eat already.

135
00:08:10,565 --> 00:08:13,485
Then we can continue to work, okay?

136
00:08:13,485 --> 00:08:16,349
Okay. Come on.

137
00:08:23,819 --> 00:08:26,159
Hurry. I don't want to be here.

138
00:08:26,159 --> 00:08:28,259
The other room is available. You can use it.

139
00:08:28,259 --> 00:08:29,714
I'm done!

140
00:08:29,714 --> 00:08:31,944
Okay. Just a second.

141
00:08:31,944 --> 00:08:34,486
I'm done here.

142
00:08:36,091 --> 00:08:37,500
What's the hurry?

143
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,652
Hey. Where have you been?

144
00:08:39,652 --> 00:08:42,353
Don't you have to conduct medical check-ups for the villagers today?

145
00:08:42,353 --> 00:08:43,893
I'm here to use the restroom.

146
00:08:43,893 --> 00:08:46,460
Dang! You really made it smelly here.

147
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:48,060
Sorry.

148
00:08:50,115 --> 00:08:55,623
Ai Fah, let me ask you something. You like Khru Prince, don't you?

149
00:08:55,623 --> 00:08:57,002
Are you crazy?

150
00:08:57,002 --> 00:08:58,968
Khru Prince? Who would like him?

151
00:08:58,968 --> 00:09:04,659
Ai Mesa said everyone who sees him will fall for him.

152
00:09:04,659 --> 00:09:06,049
Even you.

153
00:09:06,049 --> 00:09:09,187
Mesa, what is that supposed to mean?

154
00:09:09,187 --> 00:09:10,727
Don't tell me you…

155
00:09:10,727 --> 00:09:12,059
Yes.

156
00:09:12,059 --> 00:09:14,659
I think I like Khru Prince.

157
00:09:15,485 --> 00:09:17,065
They teach together.

158
00:09:17,065 --> 00:09:19,935
After spending time together, he's fallen for him.

159
00:09:19,935 --> 00:09:21,801
Well. He's cute.

160
00:09:21,801 --> 00:09:25,006
Cute? He's so cranky.

161
00:09:25,006 --> 00:09:27,367
Not just with the kids, but with me too.

162
00:09:27,367 --> 00:09:31,419
Someone like you deserves all condemnation.

163
00:09:31,419 --> 00:09:34,285
You're working with him today.

164
00:09:34,285 --> 00:09:36,185
Go and investigate for me to see if he's dating anyone.

165
00:09:36,185 --> 00:09:40,528
Are you crazy? Why does it have to be me? No.

166
00:09:40,528 --> 00:09:44,520
Well then, I won't lend you my phone from now on.

167
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,380
- Hey, relax.
- Think about it.

168
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:50,700
You can choose to be lonely at night

169
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:54,730
or call your beloved brother sometimes.

170
00:10:16,974 --> 00:10:19,372
There aren't any more patients, Khun,

171
00:10:19,372 --> 00:10:22,120
so please excuse me.

172
00:10:22,825 --> 00:10:24,802
Hold on for a second.

173
00:10:27,945 --> 00:10:30,274
Actually,

174
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:34,068
I haven't checked everyone yet.

175
00:10:35,234 --> 00:10:37,083
Who is left?

176
00:10:40,271 --> 00:10:43,124
The one in the mirror.

177
00:10:44,603 --> 00:10:48,181
Why did you dilly-dally? You could have just said it.

178
00:10:51,101 --> 00:10:53,423
Bring that chair and sit over here.

179
00:11:13,069 --> 00:11:14,723
Open your mouth.

180
00:11:27,923 --> 00:11:29,404
Everything seems fine.

181
00:11:29,404 --> 00:11:33,400
Next... I'll check your heart.

182
00:11:43,345 --> 00:11:46,394
Wait, Khun. What are you doing?

183
00:11:46,394 --> 00:11:49,457
I'm going to listen to your heart.

184
00:11:50,219 --> 00:11:53,712
I won't hear it clearly through the shirt.

185
00:11:54,441 --> 00:11:57,264
You were able to listen to other people's hearts through their shirts.

186
00:11:57,264 --> 00:11:59,064
Well.

187
00:11:59,064 --> 00:12:02,851
Everyone else got a basic check-up,

188
00:12:02,851 --> 00:12:06,969
but you get a special check-up.

189
00:12:08,859 --> 00:12:11,357
Why? Are you shy?

190
00:12:16,128 --> 00:12:18,565
I'm not.

191
00:12:18,565 --> 00:12:20,351
I'm just curious.

192
00:12:21,209 --> 00:12:22,909
Do it quickly.

193
00:12:33,957 --> 00:12:35,776
Breathe in.

194
00:12:38,598 --> 00:12:40,282
Breathe out.

195
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:02,325
Are you crazy? Khru Prince? Who would like him?

196
00:13:02,325 --> 00:13:05,118
Everyone who sees him will fall for him.

197
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:06,818
Even you.

198
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,912
You have a strong heart.

199
00:13:17,912 --> 00:13:20,707
I guess it's well taken care of.

200
00:13:20,707 --> 00:13:23,012
- Are you dating someone?
- What?

201
00:13:23,727 --> 00:13:25,712
What does that have to do with anything?

202
00:13:25,712 --> 00:13:28,432
The doctor asked you a question. You should just answer.

203
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:31,273
Why? Are you hitting on me?

204
00:13:31,273 --> 00:13:33,012
Well.

205
00:13:33,012 --> 00:13:36,715
I just want to know my patient's heart condition.

206
00:13:36,715 --> 00:13:39,936
You've been here for a while now.

207
00:13:39,936 --> 00:13:42,580
It would be quite lonely living far from your lover.

208
00:13:46,737 --> 00:13:49,129
I'm not dating anyone.

209
00:13:49,129 --> 00:13:51,975
In case that's the answer that you want to know.

210
00:13:51,975 --> 00:13:53,778
And I'm not lonely either.

211
00:13:53,778 --> 00:13:55,623
Are we done checking?

212
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,639
I'll leave now.

213
00:14:03,950 --> 00:14:07,830
[Check-up]

214
00:14:17,089 --> 00:14:18,489
Tag!

215
00:14:20,777 --> 00:14:22,577
Guys, look.

216
00:14:22,577 --> 00:14:25,899
Why is he so damn cute?

217
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:27,844
Look, Guys. I really want to be a kid.

218
00:14:27,844 --> 00:14:30,017
I want to play tag with him.

219
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:33,483
He's running so cutely.

220
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:59,846
You're exaggerating.

221
00:15:01,072 --> 00:15:02,746
Let me tell you.

222
00:15:02,746 --> 00:15:06,295
They used to have only him here.

223
00:15:06,295 --> 00:15:10,319
But now, they have Dr. Fah up here too.

224
00:15:10,319 --> 00:15:13,454
Khru Prince will surely be forgotten.

225
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:17,203
- You're so confident.
- Let me prove it to you.

226
00:15:17,203 --> 00:15:20,416
Girls. Stop. Stop.

227
00:15:20,416 --> 00:15:22,561
Stand here. Stand here.

228
00:15:22,561 --> 00:15:24,991
- I have a question for you.
- Yes?

229
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:26,917
Between…

230
00:15:27,746 --> 00:15:30,874
Khru Prince and...

231
00:15:30,874 --> 00:15:35,252
Dr. Kuafah... who is more handsome?

232
00:15:35,252 --> 00:15:37,505
It's Khru Prince, of course.

233
00:15:37,505 --> 00:15:39,661
Wow, I almost couldn't catch you!

234
00:15:39,661 --> 00:15:43,778
That's right. Khru Prince is handsome, cute, and nice.

235
00:15:43,778 --> 00:15:47,265
Dr. Kuafah has nothing on him.
- Let's go.

236
00:15:47,265 --> 00:15:51,762
- "Dr. Kuafah has nothing on him," she said.
- "Has nothing on him."

237
00:15:51,762 --> 00:15:53,517
Kids don't lie.

238
00:15:53,517 --> 00:15:56,733
Kuafah has some competition for sure.

239
00:15:56,733 --> 00:16:02,565
From Bangkok's it-boy to the mountain's loser.

240
00:16:02,565 --> 00:16:06,586
No way! I haven't lost yet.

241
00:16:06,586 --> 00:16:08,842
You'll see.

242
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:15,732
I will definitely find out Khru Prince's weakness.

243
00:16:15,732 --> 00:16:19,076
[Ban Khun Om Haet Nok School]

244
00:16:23,965 --> 00:16:26,774
- Khru, I have a question.
- Yes, Viah?

245
00:16:26,774 --> 00:16:31,715
If 2 + 2 isn't 4, then what is it?

246
00:16:31,715 --> 00:16:35,090
2 + 2 equals a rabbit.

247
00:16:35,090 --> 00:16:37,890
Gosh! You caught on. It's no fun now!

248
00:16:40,330 --> 00:16:43,785
What the heck? He can be entertaining and academic too.

249
00:16:43,785 --> 00:16:45,783
Aw!

250
00:16:48,348 --> 00:16:50,765
Not only is he capable, he doesn't care about his image.

251
00:16:50,765 --> 00:16:53,040
That's easy. Anyone can do that.

252
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:55,079
If you don't believe me, watch this.

253
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,768
Shit! I just stepped on pig dung!

254
00:17:00,768 --> 00:17:03,196
Hey, help me wash it up in the restroom.

255
00:17:03,196 --> 00:17:06,158
Thank you so much, Khru Prince. You're such a great help.

256
00:17:06,158 --> 00:17:08,245
You're welcome. We can help each other.

257
00:17:08,245 --> 00:17:10,917
- I'm feeling faint.
- Hey!

258
00:17:10,917 --> 00:17:13,647
Come, let me take you inside to rest.

259
00:17:13,647 --> 00:17:18,646
Handsome, smart, generous, and he's got a strong body.

260
00:17:18,646 --> 00:17:20,713
Nobody is perfect.

261
00:17:20,713 --> 00:17:23,050
Why do you sound so envious?

262
00:17:23,050 --> 00:17:27,105
Me? Envious? No way.

263
00:17:27,105 --> 00:17:32,400
I'll show you I'm a lot better than he is.

264
00:17:48,634 --> 00:17:52,504
Playing soccer? Can I join?

265
00:17:56,225 --> 00:18:00,474
How about we make this game more fun?

266
00:18:00,474 --> 00:18:02,213
How?

267
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:11,400
If I score, Khru Prince must take off one piece of clothing.

268
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:15,978
But if your Khru Prince can score,

269
00:18:15,978 --> 00:18:18,562
I'll take off one piece of clothing off as well.

270
00:18:20,350 --> 00:18:23,068
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

271
00:18:23,068 --> 00:18:26,191
- Right?
- Right!

272
00:18:48,202 --> 00:18:50,432
Khru Prince, go, go!

273
00:18:52,126 --> 00:18:56,917
Khru Prince, keep fighting!

274
00:18:56,917 --> 00:19:00,794
Dr. Fah, boo!

275
00:19:00,794 --> 00:19:03,530
Dr. Fah, keep fighting!

276
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:07,750
Keep fighting! Woo!

277
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:11,090
Khru Prince, keep fighting!

278
00:19:22,188 --> 00:19:23,688
Are you tired?

279
00:19:24,594 --> 00:19:26,902
I play soccer often.

280
00:19:26,902 --> 00:19:29,209
This game will not tire me out.

281
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:32,725
I meant are you tired of stalking me?

282
00:19:34,671 --> 00:19:36,371
What do you mean by stalking?

283
00:19:37,125 --> 00:19:39,338
Do you think you're a TV star?

284
00:19:39,338 --> 00:19:41,648
I have no clue what you want.

285
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:43,520
But if you have that much time,

286
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:46,660
you should spend it on taking care of the villagers.

287
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:50,062
Loong Phang, for example, who drinks every day.

288
00:19:50,062 --> 00:19:53,351
I know. We already have an appointment.

289
00:19:53,351 --> 00:19:56,251
Yes? When?

290
00:19:56,251 --> 00:20:01,215
This evening. I'll go see him after this.

291
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:04,238
I'm taking off then.

292
00:20:06,397 --> 00:20:08,763
- Wait, Khun.
- What now?

293
00:20:08,763 --> 00:20:11,645
Loong Phang's house is this way.

294
00:20:13,692 --> 00:20:15,170
I knew that!

295
00:20:15,170 --> 00:20:17,279
I just forgot.

296
00:20:21,814 --> 00:20:25,966
Dr. Fah, you're naked!

297
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,537
Why are you following me?

298
00:20:29,537 --> 00:20:31,773
- Are you trying to pick on me?
- What's your problem?

299
00:20:31,773 --> 00:20:34,386
I'm bringing something for Loong Phang.

300
00:20:55,426 --> 00:20:59,055
Why are you so shocked? Look closely.

301
00:21:01,403 --> 00:21:03,409
Oh! That's Loong Phang.

302
00:21:03,409 --> 00:21:06,309
I thought it was a dead body.

303
00:21:06,309 --> 00:21:07,848
So…

304
00:21:08,769 --> 00:21:11,512
Your hands, when will you let go?

305
00:21:14,118 --> 00:21:15,861
Sorry, Khun.

306
00:21:19,172 --> 00:21:20,672
Loong.

307
00:21:32,620 --> 00:21:36,164
He's always like this. Drunk every day.

308
00:21:36,164 --> 00:21:39,524
Sometimes he sleeps in the water basin when drunk.

309
00:21:39,524 --> 00:21:43,611
Wow! That's terrible.

310
00:21:43,611 --> 00:21:47,328
What if something happens to him?

311
00:21:48,159 --> 00:21:51,259
Everyone tries to make him quit.

312
00:21:51,259 --> 00:21:53,138
He just won't listen.

313
00:21:54,326 --> 00:21:56,740
It will be difficult then.

314
00:21:56,740 --> 00:21:58,050
What?

315
00:21:59,438 --> 00:22:02,820
I've met a lot of patients like him.

316
00:22:02,820 --> 00:22:06,005
The type that doesn't cooperate.

317
00:22:06,005 --> 00:22:11,561
When I give them advice or warning, they even talk back.

318
00:22:11,561 --> 00:22:16,606
I can't do anything more than give him treatment when he's ill.

319
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:26,459
Come with me. I will show you something.

320
00:22:41,650 --> 00:22:44,350
Who is this?

321
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:47,116
It's Loong Phang's wife.

322
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:51,180
His wife?

323
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:54,822
Where is she now?

324
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,872
She passed away.

325
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:06,745
The Village Headman told me Loong Phang and his wife

326
00:23:06,745 --> 00:23:09,972
made the best roasted pork around here in the past.

327
00:23:09,972 --> 00:23:13,511
They made it to sell at the foot of the mountain.

328
00:23:13,511 --> 00:23:16,725
Why did he stop?

329
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:25,579
After his wife died three months ago, he's just lost it.

330
00:23:25,579 --> 00:23:27,694
All he does is drink.

331
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:35,485
What's up with my patients these days?

332
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:41,598
When they get hurt, they get drunk. So bad.

333
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:46,209
Right? Just like someone around here, right?

334
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:52,905
Oops! Did I just call myself out?

335
00:24:00,150 --> 00:24:01,952
I know it's hard.

336
00:24:01,952 --> 00:24:06,852
But from now on, please take care of Loong Phang for us.

337
00:24:06,852 --> 00:24:10,684
You're probably the only person he'll listen to.

338
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:25,199
Village Headman, are you here to visit Loong Phang?

339
00:24:25,199 --> 00:24:29,792
I am. It's good you're here. I have news for you.

340
00:24:29,792 --> 00:24:31,328
What news?

341
00:24:31,328 --> 00:24:35,695
There will be a pig slaughter ritual tomorrow in the village.

342
00:24:35,695 --> 00:24:40,294
It is the pig named Gong, that the children raised.

343
00:24:40,294 --> 00:24:44,452
So please inform the children for me.

344
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:59,021
Wow! That's a tough job too.

345
00:25:01,390 --> 00:25:03,099
Good luck.

346
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:23,072
Children.

347
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:27,979
I have news for you.

348
00:25:27,979 --> 00:25:30,428
Khru, my dad is ready for the slaughter.

349
00:25:30,428 --> 00:25:32,601
What? Slaughter?

350
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:41,877
Oh, she meant rope. The Village Headman needs to use the rope for something.

351
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:46,597
Let's talk outside.

352
00:25:54,950 --> 00:25:58,099
Why did you lie to the children?

353
00:25:58,099 --> 00:26:01,364
Because I haven't told them yet.

354
00:26:01,364 --> 00:26:04,721
Ai, you must tell them right away.

355
00:26:04,721 --> 00:26:08,020
My dad says he's going to wash the pig soon.

356
00:26:08,020 --> 00:26:10,872
He's ready to kill it.

357
00:26:13,010 --> 00:26:15,301
Can you give me more time?

358
00:26:15,301 --> 00:26:20,222
I'm afraid they will be shocked if I'm not careful.

359
00:26:20,222 --> 00:26:23,079
Sure, I understand.

360
00:26:23,079 --> 00:26:27,667
But please don't take too long, or my dad will yell at me.

361
00:26:35,150 --> 00:26:37,370
[Organs of the chest and abdomen]

362
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:46,491
Hey! How did you get here?

363
00:26:49,420 --> 00:26:51,456
What is happening?

364
00:26:51,456 --> 00:26:54,896
We overheard Khru Prince say that little Gong is about to be slaughtered.

365
00:26:54,896 --> 00:26:58,223
Oh, really? Is it time?

366
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:03,983
Hearing that makes me hungry...

367
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:11,542
Hungry for some water. Why is there no water here?
(T/N: The word 'hungry' in Thai is used for both food and water)

368
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:16,341
So... why did you bring it here?

369
00:27:16,341 --> 00:27:19,210
We wanted to hide him here. We heard that

370
00:27:19,210 --> 00:27:22,780
people don't like to come here.

371
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:29,054
Khru Prince said he wouldn't come here if not necessary because Dr. Fah has bad behavior.

372
00:27:29,054 --> 00:27:34,025
What? Did Khru Prince say that? Why did he say that?

373
00:27:34,025 --> 00:27:36,028
Children. Where are you guys?

374
00:27:36,028 --> 00:27:39,515
Khru Prince is here. Let's hide little Gong.

375
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:58,442
Hey, Khun. What are you doing here?

376
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:02,234
Where is Little Gong?

377
00:28:02,234 --> 00:28:06,240
Gong? Do you mean the pig?

378
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:10,153
This is a health clinic. How can there be any pigs here?

379
00:28:10,153 --> 00:28:13,657
Yes? Then what is it under the tablecloth?

380
00:28:24,330 --> 00:28:28,292
Hey, Little Gong! When did you get here?

381
00:28:28,292 --> 00:28:31,410
He must have flown here.

382
00:28:31,410 --> 00:28:33,436
Enough with the nonsense.

383
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:38,274
[Health Clinic]

384
00:28:38,274 --> 00:28:40,887
Khru, can we spare Little Gong's life?

385
00:28:40,887 --> 00:28:43,916
Please, Khru? He's so adorable.

386
00:28:43,916 --> 00:28:48,523
Children, let me ask you something. What do you study for?

387
00:28:48,523 --> 00:28:53,733
It's our duty. When we grow up, we can lighten our parents' burdens.

388
00:28:53,733 --> 00:28:57,060
I want to study well so I can help my parents make money.

389
00:28:57,060 --> 00:29:01,207
See? We all have our duties.

390
00:29:01,207 --> 00:29:03,432
Little Gong has his duty, too.

391
00:29:03,432 --> 00:29:05,620
The Village Headman raised Little Gong

392
00:29:05,620 --> 00:29:09,770
so that one day he can be our food.

393
00:29:09,770 --> 00:29:14,550
Aren't you going to let Little Gong

394
00:29:14,550 --> 00:29:17,380
fulfill his duty?

395
00:29:28,780 --> 00:29:31,304
Goodbye, Little Gong.

396
00:29:38,590 --> 00:29:40,874
We should commence now.

397
00:29:45,690 --> 00:29:47,958
Guys, you've done great.

398
00:29:49,710 --> 00:29:51,619
Now close your eyes.

399
00:29:52,810 --> 00:29:58,241
We thank you so much, Little Gong. We wish you a heavenly afterlife.

400
00:30:25,570 --> 00:30:27,854
Hey, Khun! Khun! Khun!

401
00:30:27,854 --> 00:30:29,754
Khru Prince!

402
00:30:34,030 --> 00:30:37,138
Khun? Khun.

403
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:59,324
I guess he'd never seen anything like that. That's why he passed out.

404
00:31:00,220 --> 00:31:06,246
You may continue what you were doing. I'll take care of things here.

405
00:31:06,250 --> 00:31:09,628
Sure. Thank you, Doctor.

406
00:31:09,628 --> 00:31:11,322
Thank you so much.

407
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:28,981
I really want Ai Mesa to see you right now.

408
00:31:28,981 --> 00:31:31,678
Mr. Perfect.

409
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:46,831
Wow!

410
00:31:48,020 --> 00:31:50,438
He uses such an expensive cologne.

411
00:31:54,050 --> 00:31:56,351
This is the authentic scent.

412
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:07,209
The bag is also a designer brand.

413
00:32:09,670 --> 00:32:12,125
Who exactly is this guy?

414
00:32:18,190 --> 00:32:19,790
What's wrong?

415
00:32:21,300 --> 00:32:26,678
I'm worried about Fah. Fah has never lived a tough life like this before.

416
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:30,809
They don't have electricity. They barely have phone reception.

417
00:32:30,809 --> 00:32:33,006
Do you think he will make it?

418
00:32:33,830 --> 00:32:36,142
Please don't overthink.

419
00:32:36,142 --> 00:32:39,162
Should I call his dad

420
00:32:39,162 --> 00:32:41,488
and ask him to move Fah back here for his community service?

421
00:32:41,488 --> 00:32:43,088
Dao,

422
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:49,028
I know you're really concerned about P'Fah. But didn't you say it yourself,

423
00:32:49,028 --> 00:32:54,148
that if P'Fah went over there, he would be able to spend more time alone?

424
00:32:54,148 --> 00:32:58,977
It might be his true rest time, right?

425
00:32:59,730 --> 00:33:02,667
Yes. I hope so.

426
00:33:06,244 --> 00:33:08,413
Don't worry too much, okay?

427
00:33:08,413 --> 00:33:12,626
I made lots of your favorite foods today.

428
00:33:14,310 --> 00:33:16,968
Can I get a reward?

429
00:33:16,968 --> 00:33:18,879
No.

430
00:33:19,860 --> 00:33:21,360
Won't you give me one?

431
00:33:24,524 --> 00:33:25,946
Fine.

432
00:33:52,670 --> 00:33:53,970
Phang.

433
00:33:55,156 --> 00:33:57,103
The pig has been slaughtered.

434
00:33:57,103 --> 00:34:00,897
Don't you want to make roasted pork for everybody?

435
00:34:00,897 --> 00:34:03,083
You guys go ahead.

436
00:34:03,083 --> 00:34:04,408
Please make it.

437
00:34:04,408 --> 00:34:07,895
I know you're the best when it comes to roasted pork.

438
00:34:07,895 --> 00:34:10,383
- Is that so?
- Please do it for Little Gong.

439
00:34:10,383 --> 00:34:13,870
He would be happy if you were the one to cook him.

440
00:34:13,870 --> 00:34:18,411
- Phang.
- Please, Loong Phang? Please?

441
00:34:18,411 --> 00:34:25,185
- Please, Loong Phang?
- Please. I want to eat your roasted pork.

442
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:39,278
The villagers are waiting to eat your roasted pork.

443
00:34:39,278 --> 00:34:41,849
You're the best around here.

444
00:34:41,849 --> 00:34:44,022
Are you still not confident?

445
00:34:44,022 --> 00:34:47,748
I love you because of your roasted pork, you know?

446
00:34:47,748 --> 00:34:51,580
Stop talking. Starting roasting now.

447
00:35:27,519 --> 00:35:29,278
Finally awake?

448
00:35:36,089 --> 00:35:38,203
Did I faint?

449
00:35:38,203 --> 00:35:39,883
You did.

450
00:35:41,578 --> 00:35:47,011
Next time, if you know you are afraid of blood, don't look at it.

451
00:35:47,011 --> 00:35:50,677
You were standing there acting cool, watching them slaughter the pig.

452
00:35:51,623 --> 00:35:54,564
- What time is it?
- It's 7 p.m.

453
00:35:54,564 --> 00:35:56,049
What?

454
00:35:56,049 --> 00:35:58,764
- We're late.
- For what?

455
00:35:58,764 --> 00:36:02,423
Come on. Follow me. We're late for the celebration.

456
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:16,941
It took you long enough to come.

457
00:36:16,941 --> 00:36:19,798
What is this?

458
00:36:22,705 --> 00:36:24,883
It's the welcoming party for the four of you.

459
00:36:24,883 --> 00:36:27,480
It's our village's tradition.

460
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:31,295
We throw a party to officially welcome new visitors.

461
00:36:31,295 --> 00:36:34,409
Let's join them. The party is about to start.

462
00:36:34,409 --> 00:36:35,709
Come on.

463
00:36:38,667 --> 00:36:41,143
Why don't you wait for me?

464
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,560
Thank you.

465
00:36:54,562 --> 00:36:56,441
Come dance with us.

466
00:36:58,120 --> 00:37:02,030
There you go. It looks cool.

467
00:37:02,030 --> 00:37:04,182
Let's go dance.

468
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:08,548
Only him?

469
00:37:19,140 --> 00:37:22,438
The locals are so nice.

470
00:37:24,140 --> 00:37:26,491
This is how they are.

471
00:37:26,491 --> 00:37:29,467
Are you done dancing?

472
00:37:30,810 --> 00:37:33,847
♫ Taking a journey, no matter how far the horizon ♫

473
00:37:33,847 --> 00:37:35,201
Let's go dance together.

474
00:37:35,201 --> 00:37:40,060
♫ No matter how high or steep the mountain ♫

475
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:48,050
♫ But in the end, it's too late, love vanished ♫

476
00:38:14,820 --> 00:38:19,013
Dao. Loong Phang's roasted pork is so good.

477
00:38:19,013 --> 00:38:20,535
When I go back to Bangkok,

478
00:38:20,535 --> 00:38:25,410
I'll ask him to make some for you. Would you like that?

479
00:38:25,410 --> 00:38:26,900
Really?

480
00:38:27,554 --> 00:38:29,588
But I think it's kind of odd.

481
00:38:29,588 --> 00:38:34,280
You sound happy somehow.

482
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:36,822
Because Loong Phang's pork is just so good.

483
00:38:36,822 --> 00:38:38,468
Really?

484
00:38:38,468 --> 00:38:41,780
But I think there's more to the story.

485
00:38:41,780 --> 00:38:45,960
Tell me honestly. You're not flirting with someone up there, are you?

486
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:49,635
Are you crazy? Oops! I'm being loud again.

487
00:38:51,310 --> 00:38:53,113
Dao, I have to go.

488
00:38:53,113 --> 00:38:54,866
The house owner is coming.

489
00:38:54,866 --> 00:38:58,141
- Sure.
- Okay. Talk to you later.

490
00:39:02,554 --> 00:39:04,990
Hey, Khun.

491
00:39:04,990 --> 00:39:06,846
Is this your house?

492
00:39:06,846 --> 00:39:08,376
Of course.

493
00:39:08,977 --> 00:39:13,333
You brought me here this evening. Don't you remember?

494
00:39:13,992 --> 00:39:15,675
Really?

495
00:39:16,684 --> 00:39:18,660
I don't remember.

496
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:24,446
So… Did you just talk to your lover?

497
00:39:24,446 --> 00:39:27,009
Why do you want to know?

498
00:39:27,009 --> 00:39:29,083
Are you hitting on me?

499
00:39:30,157 --> 00:39:31,957
That's not it.

500
00:39:31,957 --> 00:39:36,610
You talk to someone so sweetly every night.

501
00:39:36,610 --> 00:39:38,733
I'm just curious.

502
00:39:39,770 --> 00:39:43,619
For someone who fainted, you sure talk back well.

503
00:39:43,619 --> 00:39:45,950
I guess you're feeling better.

504
00:39:48,390 --> 00:39:50,348
Of course.

505
00:39:50,348 --> 00:39:52,552
I ate Loong Phang's roasted pork,

506
00:39:52,552 --> 00:39:54,712
therefore I'm completely healed.

507
00:39:54,712 --> 00:39:56,478
That's good.

508
00:39:56,478 --> 00:40:00,084
Loong Phang said he'll quit drinking,

509
00:40:00,084 --> 00:40:02,687
and you're fully recovered.

510
00:40:02,687 --> 00:40:08,028
That means everyone in the village is healthy now.

511
00:40:09,242 --> 00:40:12,783
Not yet. There's still one person left.

512
00:40:12,783 --> 00:40:14,383
Who?

513
00:40:21,068 --> 00:40:22,768
Right here.

514
00:40:31,158 --> 00:40:33,124
Did you mean me?

515
00:40:34,540 --> 00:40:36,242
Yes, of course.

516
00:40:36,910 --> 00:40:41,230
You're taking care of everyone, but please try to take care of yourself too.

517
00:40:41,230 --> 00:40:46,350
How will you convince the villagers to take care of themselves

518
00:40:46,350 --> 00:40:49,154
if all you do is drink

519
00:40:49,990 --> 00:40:52,371
and don't eat when you work.

520
00:40:55,550 --> 00:40:57,774
I get it now.

521
00:40:57,774 --> 00:40:59,675
I will take care of myself, okay?

522
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:04,602
All right. Please excuse me now.

523
00:41:06,915 --> 00:41:11,110
Thanks for taking care of me when I passed out.

524
00:41:11,110 --> 00:41:14,200
And I want to thank you as well...

525
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:18,190
for helping me do the check-ups the other day.

526
00:41:22,934 --> 00:41:25,808
Hey! Hold on, Khun.

527
00:41:30,460 --> 00:41:31,770
Well...

528
00:41:33,140 --> 00:41:37,887
I saw that you had designer-brand cologne in your room.

529
00:41:37,887 --> 00:41:40,461
Is it yours?

530
00:41:40,461 --> 00:41:43,460
What? You saw that?

531
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:44,731
Why?

532
00:41:44,731 --> 00:41:47,229
Are you afraid people will know you're rich?

533
00:41:47,229 --> 00:41:49,329
It's the opposite.

534
00:41:49,329 --> 00:41:51,912
It's a fake one from a market.

535
00:41:51,912 --> 00:41:53,840
It was only 300 baht.

536
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:59,106
I'm not supporting counterfeit products, but the merchant was very persistent.

537
00:41:59,106 --> 00:42:01,568
Please excuse me, Khun.

538
00:42:36,370 --> 00:42:38,980
I almost got found out.

539
00:42:48,950 --> 00:42:54,160
When we find something that makes us feel at ease, we want to keep it for a long time.

540
00:42:57,730 --> 00:43:01,445
